<p>I wanted to put <strong><code>ImageB</code></strong> on top of <strong><code>ImageA</code></strong>. How should I achieve that?</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/k4WJ7.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/k4WJ7.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Note:</p>  <ul> <li>I don't want to fix my height for both images so that I can maintain their aspect ratio.</li> <li><p>The height for <strong><code>ImageA</code></strong> and <strong><code>ImageB</code></strong> are different.</p>  <p> </p>  <pre><code>&lt;RelativeLayout     android:layout_height="wrap_content"     android:layout_width="match_parent"&gt;      &lt;ImageView     android:id="@+id/imageA"     android:layout_height="wrap_content"     android:layout_width="match_parent"     android:scaleType="fitCenter"     android:src="@drawable/imageA"      android:adjustViewBounds="true"/&gt;      &lt;!-- How to let imageB matches imageA's height ? --&gt;     &lt;ImageView     android:id="@+id/imageB"         android:layout_height="match_parent"         android:layout_width="wrap_content"         android:layout_alignParentRight="true"         android:layout_alignParentTop="true"         android:src="@drawable/imageB"/&gt; &lt;/RelativeLayout&gt; </code></pre>  <p></p></li> </ul>  <p>Any help will be appreciated. </p>